    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I was a vegan for about 8 years, but had never tried an oyster before that time despite my love of seafood. Now that I&#39;m a carnivore again, I&#39;ve been eating all sorts of stuff that my life-long meat-eating family won&#39;t even touch: bison, liver, salmon skin. But I still haven&#39;t indulged in oysters. Now you&#39;ve inspired to seek them out! Living on the West Coast (Vancouver), that shouldn&#39;t be too hard! 😉</p>
    </div>

