    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I love this. And I think I am close to the 225 year mark. The last- and only- oyster I ate was when I was about 13. So it&#39;s been 20 years, I suppose. I tried to swallow it- they pulled it right out of the water onto the boat where I was traveling on an 8th grade trip and it stuck in my throat. I could not get it down, I gagged, and coughed it out. </p>
<p>This boy then snatched it- ew ew ew- and made my friend Tori swear she&#39;d go out with him if he ate it. They went on only one date, but I have never eaten another oyster. </p>
<p>However, your post does give me hope.</p>
    </div>

